		<div class="row">
			<div class="five columns animation-toggle">
				<input type="checkbox" class="animateSVG" name="animateSVG">
				<label for="animateSVG">Animate SVG</label>
				<!-- @include components/_svg-animation.svg -->
			</div>
			<div class="seven columns">
				<p>I like CSS. I just kind of get it. And I'm pretty gosh darn alright at making CSS do what I want. This is an animation I made using just CSS and an SVG &mdash; no JavaScript required.</p>
					<p>Abusing CSS like this is an absolute dog as far as performance goes, but I was <i>seriously</i> procrastinating some real work.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

